To run iatclsh, set environment variables IATCLSH_HOME and PATH. Use command
line parameter '-config' to specify a configuration file. Files to source are
also specified on the command line. 

For example, to run iatclsh with provided example files with Linux:

    #!/bin/bash
    export IATCLSH_HOME=~/iatclsh
    export PATH=$PATH:$IATCLSH_HOME/sh
    cd $IATCLSH_HOME/examples
    iatclsh -bg example_config.tcl ia_example_hw.tcl

And an example for Windows:

    set IATCLSH_HOME=%HOMEPATH%\iatclsh
    set PATH=%PATH%;%IATCLSH_HOME%\win
    cd %IATCLSH_HOME%\examples
    iatclsh -bg example_config.tcl ia_example_hw.tcl

Tcl/Tk is required, at least version 8.5. Change files under sh/win for use 
with different versions of Tcl and Tk.

